      {
        "id": "docling_scihub_iccwamtip51612.2020.9317329.pdf_4_2",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In this research, we used a deep learning method focused on Fusion CNN architecture to derive facial patches and depth of 3 types of human facial image samples namely Color, Depth and IR from the CASIA-SURF dataset modeled with an altered 3D convolutional neural network classifier. Our primary interest was to be able to extract facial patches and the depth levels of all 3 facial inputs stated earlier on to distinguish a real face from a spoofed face from a CASIASURF dataset provided which are not preprocessed.",
        "bbox": [
          0.09240246874375913,
          0.31686046552252395,
